["It's just a matter of marketing and promoting ourselves," ]54 [says
Headley Bell, a fifth-generation horse breeder from Lexington. ]55

[Maybe it's not that simple. ]56 [For starters, racehorse buyers have
to remember the basic problem of such ventures: ]57 [These beasts
don't come with warranties. ]58 [And for every champion, there are
plenty of nags. ]59 [Katherine Voss, a veteran trainer at the Laurel,
Md., track, offers neophytes a sobering tour of a horse barn, ]60
[noting ]61 [that only three of about a dozen horses have won sizable
purses. ]62

[One brown two-year-old filly was wheezing from a cold, ]63 [while
another had splints on its legs, ]64 [keeping both animals from the
